&TUTORIAL ----------- JTIP UTILITY - SHOW JOB NAMES / ID'S ------------ TUTORIAL
&NEXT SELECTION ===>%SELECT                             &
$
   THE&SHOW JOBS$FUNCTION ( OPTION&L$) IS USED TO DISPLAY THE STATUS OF
   A JOB OR JOBS.

   FILL IN THE FOLLOWING FIELDS OF THE JTIP UTILITY MENU:
       - ENTER&L$IN THE SELECT OPTION FIELD.

   THE FOLLOWING RULES APPLY FOR THE&JOBNAME/JOBID$PARAMETER WHEN USED
   WITH THE&L$OPTION:

       -&JOBNAME/ID$= BLANK - ALL JOBS THAT HAVE JOB NAMES BEGINNING WITH
                              THE USER'S ID WILL BE DISPLAYED.
       -&JOBNAME$   = USERID + ONE CHARACTER - SAME AS BLANK.
       -&JOBNAME/ID$= ANYTHING ELSE - ONLY THE NAMED JOB WILL BE DISPLAYED.

<ACTION>
1 SELECT CHAR(36) CURSOR;
2 SELECT CHAR(8) LIST(' ') RETURN(' ');
3 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTJTIP  ');
4 * CHAR(8) INIT('VTJTIP2 ');
5 * CHAR(8) INIT('        ');
<END>
